In many hospitals it is saved with the disinfectants
This anus have been registered in hospitals several thousands of infections produced by the improper application of the antibiotics in the first place.
The prevailing circumstances of hygiene in hospitals, the crowded of the beds and the overload of the staff do not favor the control of the infections - it states the medical one-department head of the National Center of Epidemiology.
In many hospitals it is saved even with the disinfectants.
Not long ago an infection with MRSA has been diagnosed in the department of traumatology of the Hospital János.
In a man hospitalized after a severe accident the presence of the bacterium resistant to the antibiotics was detected.
The patient was isolated.
The same type of infection took place in this same hospital at the beginning of the anus.
To one wounded of a severe automotive accident they gave it discharge of the hospital and the same patient little afterwards had to go back to the hospital as a result of the infection with MRSA and since then an important operation for the presence of the bacterium in its organism has not been able to be carried out.
Up to the 10 of December of this anus cases of hospital infection produced by multiresistentes agents have been registered in the National System Nosocomialis Surveillance 1094 - said Karolina Böröcz, medical-department head of the National Center of Epidemiology.
This means that in the hospitals with every safety this quantity of infections produced by multiresistentes agents has been registered, of the rest it is not had information.
Near the two third parts of the infections (683 cases) they owe to the MRSA, that is to the Staphylococcus aureus, resistant to the meticilina-oxacilina.
A third of the human beings they take the bacterium of Staphylococcus aureus (SA) in its nose without causing any illness.
The infections produced by the SA (for ej.: inflammation of the throat, amygdalitis, skin infections, infections of wounds) react well to the antibiotics and are of easy treatment.
However, once it is applied exaggerated or, improperly to the antibiotics the bacteria that normally react well to the antibiotics, are transformed into bacteria very resistant to the antibiotics and contaminate quickly in inadequate hospital conditions.
They can cause severe hospital infections, for example infections of wounds or septicemia in the first place to the patients with temporary or chronic immunodeficiency, to patients with the weakened organism, to elders or to people of little peso.
In the view of the doctor-director of the Hospital János there is not at all special in the infection of the MRSA, these infections are daily in hospitals.
The infection must not be confused with the epidemic, the MRSA only is absent - it said Tibor Nyulasi - where its presence is not examined.
Resistant to the antibiotics
"These patients are isolated, the staff of infirmary attends them in rubber gloves and mask and there are the adequate antibiotics for its treatment" - it said Tibor Nyulasi.
The hospitalized patients are examined previously to verify the presence of the MRSA in its organism, but not even like this can be avoided the infection in all the cases.
It is not in fashion to take exhibitions
It would be possible to prevent the hospital infections of the MRSA in most of the cases, however the current national hospital circumstances do not favor for the prevention of the formation and the infection with the multiresistentes pathogenic agents - it states Karolina Böröcz.
As this infection is produced fundamentally in hospitals and amenity centers, the hospitals should examine the hospitalized patients and to isolate immediately to you fall ill them that they take the MRSA in its organism.
However, in the Hungarian hospitals the sampling is not in fashion microbiological.
This fact is due also to the National Box of Health not financing these medical examinations.
So that most of the cases come out to the public light when the infections of the MRSA visible in the patient - it said the medical one-are already produced department head of the epidemiological center.
The European Union does rigorous commanderies for the application of the antibiotics in the human medicine and there are also national directives to treat the infections and pathological frames.
There is that empenarse in which the therapy with antibiotic is directed, that is, microbiological examinations to prevent that are produced by endurance in front of the medicines should be done, but the hospitals not always comply with this demand.
The sampling microbiological are still less frequent in the case of the itinerant patients or in the basic assistance - it stated Karolina Böröcz.
It is saved with the disinfectants
The scientific experiments have proved to another that in most of the cases the MRSA contaminates of a patient through the sanitary staff.
Therefore, desempenan a very important paper the washed of the hands, the use of rubber gloves and of masks, however also in this meaning are experimented considerable mistakes in hospitals.
The MRSA is contaminated through the transmission for drops and the direct contact among people, however in the national hospital circumstances is not always possible to isolate the contaminated patient.
It is more, the rooms of the hospitals frequently are crowded, the beds many times are very joint, although to prevent the epidemic, the patients should be separated at least by a distance from 1.5 meters.
Regrettably it can also be experimented on - it added Karolina Böröcz - that in the hospitals of less favorable economic situation it is saved with the disinfectants, there are few male nurses and many patients and because of that there is a bigger probability for the infection.
In the view of Karolina Böröcz, where the adequate measures of prevention are complied with, less infections of this type are registered or the infection of the pathogenic agent can stop.
Governmental program against the MRSA
The treatment of the infection with MRSA is an enormous expense for the National Background of Health Insurance, therefore in all the countries people fight against it.
In England there is for example a governmental program to prevent and to reduce the cases of the MRSA.
Apparently the program has successes, according to the supplied data, the infections with MRSA show trend of decrease in England.
The European Center for the Prevention and the Control of the Illnesses (ECDC) has among its priorities the prevention of the multiresistentes agents (among these the MRSA) and that of the hospital infections that owe to these pathogenic agents.
